<TITLE> Danida official, driver abducted in Bandarban </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, June 26 (bdnews24.com)  An armed gang Monday abducted a Danish International Development Agency official, Suman Sharif, and his driver Mohammad Hanif from Keuburipara in Thanchi upazila of Bandarban. Bandarban CID police inspector Rustam Ali said that Suman Sharif, on his way back to town at about 4:30 pm, was kidnapped by 10 to 12 armed men in Keubaripara, nine kilometres from Thanchi. On information, police and BDR led by additional police super Mosharaf Hossain Miazi visited the spot. BDR detained one Keuburi Marma from Keuburi Tuesday morning. He was being interrogated. Deputy commissioner Abdul Majid Shah Akhand, district police super Abdul Kader and senior military officers held a meeting Tuesday at Bandarban cantonment. bdnews
